9:
The photos. That's what they are,
right? Snapshots of memories. I
have no interest in them.
10:
Don't get me wrong. Keeping
records is essential... but photos are
different. They're not necessary to
keep moving forward.
11:
They're... a comfort. They put your
mind at ease when you fail to make
progress. They're an opiate for when
you get stuck.
15:
Who knows. Maybe you really need
them. If that's the case, then you
should take good care of them.
17:
Either that, or throw them all away
and move forward... 
By my side.
19:
I thought so.
You and I... really are quite different.
21:
No matter. Where shall we go next?
There's a deserted island up north
where we can lay low. Finally, things
are getting interesting!
24:
I'm no good... Narcissa and my
father both knew it. They're right.
26:
I'm empty inside... And I'm weak. I
just get in the way and rely on
people. I cause them problems... Like
I've done with you.
29:
I don't deserve to be helped... by
anyone!
35:
So please, no more! Just... leave me
be!
39:
No way. I can't get behind a single
thing you're saying, Echo.
42:
We heard how much that place
meant to you, loud and clear!
45:
You want to go there, so we want to
take you! We feel the same way
about this!
55:
You... you're all kind and honest
people... Strong enough to move
ahead.
58:
But me? I'm pathetic... A weak girl
who can't do anything by herself. I'd
only get in your way.
64:
I can't go with you. I'm sorry. I really
am.
80:
None of that matters! Strong or
weak? Who cares! You're YOU, Echo!
84:
Don't say things like that... Please,
don't push us away!
91:
It's just... it DOES matter. Your
strength is what lets you get
through the day with a smile.
94:
If I were gone, no one would miss
me. Little old pathetic me... Everyone
would be better off without me!
98:
We KNOW you're weak, Echo. We
knew from the very beginning—it's
not a secret!
101:
But you know what? I'm weak too. I
know what it's like!
104:
To hate yourself for being weak... To
be afraid of failing and getting hurt...
108:
That's why I felt I could relate to you!
I wanted to laugh and smile and cry
alongside you!
116:
To show you that pain can be
shared! That when you feel sad, you
can reach out to others! I just...
120:
I don't understand why you'd
abandon us like this! You... you're a
liar, Echo!
